<header>
    <h1>The Importance of Brake Pad and Piston Lubrication</h1>
</header>

<main>
    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Why Lubricate Brake Pads and Pistons?</h2>
        <p>Brake pads and pistons are critical components in the braking system. Over time, these parts can become stiff, corroded, or clogged with dirt and debris, which impacts braking performance. Proper lubrication and servicing can extend the lifespan of these components and ensure smooth, safe operation.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Applying Brake Grease to the Guide Pins</h2>
        <p>Applying brake grease to the guide pins helps prevent them from seizing up due to heat and friction. This ensures that the brake pads can move freely, reducing wear and tear and improving braking efficiency.</p>
        <img src="file:///C:/Users/Kal%20Tire/Downloads/Lubricating-Brake-Pad-Guide-Pins-1652279880926.jpg" alt="Applying grease to brake guide pins">
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Servicing the Brake Pads</h2>
        <p>Brake pads should be lubricated on their back surfaces and mounting tabs (never the front). This reduces noise and prevents sticking, which can cause uneven wear. Proper lubrication on the back of brake pads can also help dissipate heat.</p>
        <img src="file:///C:/Users/Kal%20Tire/Downloads/ceramic-brake-lubricant-236ml-874803ce-1ed5-4c5d-afc3-03512aa31470-jpgrendition.jpg" alt="Applying lubricant to brake pads">
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Where to Apply Brake Grease on Disk Brakes</h2>
        <p>The illustration below shows the recommended points for applying brake grease on disk brakes, including the caliper bushings, pins, and the back of the pads. Proper application ensures longevity and optimal performance of brake components.</p>
        <img src="file:///C:/Users/Kal%20Tire/Downloads/Disc-Brake-Greasing_4-2000.jpg" alt="Illustration showing where to apply brake grease on disk brakes "style="width: 50%;">
    </section>
